properties.Name: SangerFormat
properties.Description: Sanger format can encode a Phred quality score from 0 to 93 using ASCII 33 to 126 (although in raw read data the Phred quality score rarely exceeds 60, higher scores are possible in assemblies or read maps)

Columns.Description: The Phred quality score is a measure of the quality of the identification of the nucleobases generated by automated DNA sequencing.
